<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37933#p37933</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37933#p37933"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Pegs - ROM and Source]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37933#p37933"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Roth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Okay, so if I have bit 2 of $2000 always set to zero, that will mean that I have the screen arranged horizontally, right?<br /></div><br />The meaning of the NT bits in $2000 change according to how the mirroring is set physically in the cart.<br /><br />The thing is that Nintendo uses a different terminology than the iNES header. What iNES calls vertical mirroring, is represented by an "H" in NES boards, and vice versa. iNES refers to what is mirrored, and Nintendo to what isn't.<br /><br />EDIT: Just noticed you said "bit 2 of $2000", which has nothing to do with mirroring. Did you mean bit 1?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Tue Sep 30, 2008 3:16 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
