<author><name><![CDATA[tepples]]></name></author>
<updated>2008-09-24T13:12:25-07:00</updated>
<published>2008-09-24T13:12:25-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37520#p37520</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37520#p37520"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Pegs - ROM and Source]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4398&amp;p=37520#p37520"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Roth wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />As for the registers thing, well, that's something I just can't get used to. I find it easier to remember what a register is and what it does by it's number rather than a name. For example, when I hear PPUADDR or PPUMASK, I think... umm, what is that? I can never remember what it's (usual) associative name is.<br /></div><br />I guess my preference for register names just comes from my GBA background, where there are about an order of magnitude more PPU registers, some of them organized into arrays of registers. It's common in C on the GBA or DS to, say, write a huge OR expression with a half-dozen flags and assign it to one of the four BGCTRL registers (which roughly correspond to PPUCTRL on the NES, one for each layer).<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">BGCTRL&#91;1&#93; = CHAR_BASE&#40;0&#41; | BG_16_COLOR | BG_WID_64 | BG_HT_32 | SCREEN_BASE&#40;30&#41;;</div><br />This sets up layer 1 (of 0-3) to use pattern table 0 (of 0-3), 4-bit tiles (not 8-bit), vertical mirroring (not horizontal, 1-screen, or 4-screen), and nametables 30 and 31 (of 0-31, where each nametable overlaps 8 pattern tables).<br /><br />kyuusaku: The problem with comments is that they quickly go out of sync with the code.<br /><br />Here's the nes.h that I've been using in one of my projects:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">PPUCTRL = $2000<br />NT_2000 = $00<br />NT_2400 = $01<br />NT_2800 = $02<br />NT_2C00 = $03<br />VRAM_DOWN = $04<br />OBJ_0000 = $00<br />OBJ_1000 = $08<br />OBJ_8X16 = $20<br />BG_0000 = $00<br />BG_1000 = $10<br />VBLANK_NMI = $80<br /><br />PPUMASK = $2001<br />LIGHTGRAY = $01<br />BG_OFF = $00<br />BG_CLIP = $08<br />BG_ON = $0A<br />OBJ_OFF = $00<br />OBJ_CLIP = $10<br />OBJ_ON = $14<br /><br />PPUSTATUS = $2002<br />OAMADDR = $2003<br />PPUSCROLL = $2005<br />PPUADDR = $2006<br />PPUDATA = $2007<br /><br />OAM_DMA = $4014<br />SNDCHN = $4015<br />P1 = $4016<br />P2 = $4017<br /><br />KEY_A      = %10000000<br />KEY_B      = %01000000<br />KEY_SELECT = %00100000<br />KEY_START  = %00010000<br />KEY_UP     = %00001000<br />KEY_DOWN   = %00000100<br />KEY_LEFT   = %00000010<br />KEY_RIGHT  = %00000001<br /><br /></div><br />(How come I can get away with pasting code, but jargon can't?)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Sep 24, 2008 1:12 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
